<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-13T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-13T05:00:00-05:00" n="921" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.51/501: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-13T11:00:00+01:00">June
                                        13, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 13—8:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>187. My 186. Since my instructions regarding possible aid to Spain
                                emphasize that such assistance would be predicated upon the
                                maintenance of Spanish neutrality,<note n="7" xml:id="d921fn7">See
                                    instruction dated May 28, <ref target="#pg_803">p.
                                    803</ref>.</note> and since the declaration of non-belligerence
                                by the Spanish Government has, in the strict sense, terminated
                                Spain’s neutral status, urgently request new instructions regarding
                                my interview with Franco.</p>
                            <p>Will appreciate these instructions by tonight at latest since the
                                interview may take place tomorrow.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>